cmd history removal for currect session: 
history -c

Don't want save history for future session to disable:
export HISTSIZE=0
export HISTFILESIZE=0
source ~/.bashrc


re enable:
export HISTSIZE=1000   # or any other number, like 5000, for the number of commands to keep
export HISTFILESIZE=2000  # or any other number for the file size limit
source ~/.bashrc # After modifying the ~/.bashrc file, reload it with the following command to apply the changes
touch ~/.bash_history # If you deleted the .bash_history file, simply recreate it:
history

